text: Naumovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Naumovsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 2,935 as of 2010. There are 27 streets. == Geography == It is located 12 km from Sterlitamak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Naumovka
